Chevys are pretty good &quot;Drag&quot; vehicles.  I drag one behind my Ford when it comes time to spread chicken manure onto the fields (Can't afford a cheap trailer... but the Chevy... well I don't have to wash it out when I'm finished!)<br><br>
The reverse of the question I asked you... is what I am having to deal with, Why did I march off to war?  I, too, feared not coming home alive.  I didn't allow myself to think going there was wrong.  I'll spare you the surface answers and try to expose the real reasons why I went.  First, I must disconnect the hindsight terminal, if possible.<br><br>
If America is attacked, I choose to believe that you would fight.  I would like to have you in my outfit... at least then, I wouldn't be the dumbest one on the hill... the ugliest one in ranks.  If the initial attack occurs far from where you live, try an hop a ride in a Ford.  Otherwise, you may arrive too late to see any real action.<br><br>
On the other hand, you might just be a pain in the neck.  I would probably have to add two or three hair spray bearors to the mortar platoon.<br>
MTF<br>
